qas.question: Have the changes in Burmese law been of benefit to the country in international views ?

answers.text: approval of Myanmar's bid for the position of ASEAN chair in 2014; the visit by United States Secretary of State Hillary Clinton

qas.question: Who was the United States Secretary of State who visited Myanmar in 2014?
How long was the interval between the visits from the United States Secretary of State officials ?
What political party does Aung San Suu Kyi belong to ?

context: The impact of the post-election reforms has been observed in numerous areas, including ASEAN's <a0_0>approval of Myanmar's bid for the position of ASEAN chair in 2014; the visit by United States <a1_0>Secretary of State Hillary Clinton<a1_0/><a0_0/> in December 2011 for the encouragement of further progress—it was the first visit by a Secretary of State in <a2_0>more than fifty years<a2_0/> (Clinton met with the Burmese president and former military commander Thein Sein, as well as opposition leader Aung San Suu Kyi); and the participation of Aung San Suu Kyi's <a3_0>National League for Democracy (NLD) party<a3_0/> in the 2012 by-elections, facilitated by the government's abolition of the laws that previously barred the NLD. As of July 2013, about 100 political prisoners remain imprisoned, while conflict between the Burmese Army and local insurgent groups continues.
